This paper involves deep learning techniques for image processing and medical imaging, which are commonly found in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging data and lung pathology detection, which could also place it in the medical informatics (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of simulated X-rays and CT scans for training the FCNNs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
